 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Debt obligations </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The
Company has incurred debt obligations principally through public and private offerings and bank loans. There are no provisions in the Company&#146;s debt obligations that would accelerate repayment of debt as a result of a change in credit ratings
or a material adverse change in the Company&#146;s business. Certain of the Company&#146;s debt obligations contain cross-acceleration provisions, and restrictions on Company and subsidiary mortgages and the long-term debt of certain subsidiaries.
Under certain agreements, the Company has the option to retire debt prior to maturity, either at par or at a premium over par. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The
following table summarizes the Company&#146;s debt obligations. (Interest rates reflected in the table include the effects of interest rate and foreign currency exchange agreements.) </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

and other guarantees </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Borrowings related to the ESOP at December&nbsp;31, 2006, which include $79.1 million of loans from the Company to the ESOP, are
reflected as long-term debt with a corresponding reduction of shareholders&#146; equity (additional paid-in capital included a balance of $71.1 million and $77.4 million at December&nbsp;31, 2006 and 2005 respectively). The ESOP is repaying the
loans and interest through 2018 using Company contributions and dividends from its McDonald&#146;s common stock holdings. As the principal amount of the borrowings is repaid, the debt and the unearned ESOP compensation (additional paid-in capital)
are being reduced. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Company also has guaranteed certain affiliate and other loans totaling $11.8 million at December&nbsp;31, 2006.
These guarantees are contingent commitments generally issued by the Company to support borrowing arrangements of certain U.S. partnerships and franchisees, and certain affiliates outside the U.S. The terms of the guarantees vary and are equal to the
remaining term of the related debt. At December&nbsp;31, 2006, there was no carrying value for obligations under these guarantees in the Consolidated balance sheet. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>EMPLOYEE BENEFIT PLANS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">The Company&#146;s Profit Sharing and Savings Plan for U.S.-based employees includes a 401(k) feature, a leveraged employee stock ownership (ESOP) feature, and a discretionary employer profit sharing match. The 401(k) feature allows
participants to make pretax contributions that are partly matched from shares released under the ESOP. The Profit Sharing and Savings Plan also provides for a discretionary employer profit sharing match at the end of the year for eligible
participants who have contributed to the 401(k) feature. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">All contributions and related earnings can be invested in several investment
alternatives as well as McDonald&#146;s common stock in accordance with each participant&#146;s elections. Effective January&nbsp;1, 2007, participants&#146; future contributions to the 401(k) feature and the discretionary employer match are limited
to 20% investment in McDonald&#146;s Common stock. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Employees of Boston Market participate in a separate retirement plan known as the
McDonald&#146;s Ventures 401(k) Plan. The Ventures Plan includes 401(k) and matching features. The investment alternatives for the Ventures Plan are identical to the McDonald&#146;s Profit Sharing and Savings Plan. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Company also maintains certain supplemental benefit plans. At the end of 2004, the Company froze the nonqualified, unfunded Supplemental Plan that it
previously maintained due to changes under Section&nbsp;409A of the Internal Revenue Code, so that no new contributions or changes will be made to the Supplemental Plan. Effective January&nbsp;1, 2005, the Company adopted a new nonqualified,
unfunded Excess Benefit and Deferred Bonus Plan that allows participants to (i)&nbsp;make tax-deferred contributions and (ii)&nbsp;receive Company-provided allocations that cannot be made under the Profit Sharing and Savings Plan and Ventures 401(k)
Plan because of Internal Revenue Service limitations. The investment alternatives and returns in the Excess Benefit and Deferred Bonus Plan, and also the frozen Supplemental Plan, are based on certain market-rate investment alternatives under the
Profit Sharing and Savings Plan. Total combined liabilities under the frozen Supplemental Plan and the Excess Benefit and Deferred Bonus Plan were $378.6 million at December&nbsp;31, 2006 and $366.5 million at December&nbsp;31, 2005 and were
included in other long-term liabilities in the Consolidated balance sheet. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Company has entered into derivative contracts to hedge
market-driven changes in certain of the Supplemental Plan and Excess Benefit and Deferred Bonus Plan liabilities. At December&nbsp;31, 2006, derivatives with a fair value of $91.5 million indexed to the Company&#146;s stock as well as an investment
totaling $78.2 million indexed to certain market indices were included in miscellaneous other assets in the Consolidated balance sheet. All changes in liabilities for these nonqualified plans and in the fair value of the derivatives are recorded in
selling, general&nbsp;&amp; administrative expenses. Changes in fair value of the derivatives indexed to the Company&#146;s stock are recorded in the income statement because the contracts provide the counterparty with a choice to settle in cash or
shares. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Total U.S. costs for the Profit Sharing and Savings Plan and Ventures 401(k) Plan, including nonqualified benefits and related
hedging activities, were (in millions): 2006&#150;$61.9; 2005&#150;$59.9; 2004&#150;$58.5. Certain subsidiaries outside the U.S. also offer profit sharing, pension, stock purchase or other similar benefit plans. Total plan costs outside the U.S.
were (in millions): 2006&#150;$69.8; 2005&#150;$54.1; 2004&#150;$47.8. The total combined liabilities for the international pension plans of $127.9 million, which were in a limited number of markets, were primarily included in other long-term
liabilities in the Consolidated balance sheet. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Other postretirement benefits and postemployment benefits were immaterial. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>PROPERTY AND EQUIPMENT </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Net property and equipment consisted of:

FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">From time to time, the Company is subject to proceedings, lawsuits and other claims related to competitors, customers, employees, franchisees, government agencies, intellectual property, shareholders and suppliers.
The Company is required to assess the likelihood of any adverse judgments or outcomes to these matters as well as potential ranges of probable losses. A determination of the amount of accrual required, if any, for these contingencies is made after
careful analysis of each matter. The required accrual may change in the future due to new developments in each matter or changes in approach such as a change in settlement strategy in dealing with these matters. The Company does not believe that any
such matter currently being reviewed will have a material adverse effect on its financial condition or results of operations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>SHARE-BASED COMPENSATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">At December&nbsp;31, 2006, the Company had a share-based compensation plan, which authorizes the granting of various equity-based incentives including stock options and restricted stock units (RSUs) to employees and nonemployee directors.
The number of shares of common stock reserved for issuance under the plans was 155.3&nbsp;million at December&nbsp;31, 2006, including 50.8&nbsp;million available for future grants. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Stock options </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Stock options to purchase common stock are granted with an exercise price equal to the closing market
price of the Company&#146;s stock on the date of grant. Substantially all of the options become exercisable in four equal installments, beginning a year from the date of the grant, and generally expire 10 years from the grant date. Options granted
between May&nbsp;1, 1999 and December&nbsp;31, 2000 (approximately 26&nbsp;million options currently outstanding) expire 13 years from the date of grant. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Intrinsic value for stock options is defined as the difference between the current market value and the exercise price. During 2006 and 2005, the total intrinsic value of stock options exercised was $412.6 million and
$290.9 million, respectively. Cash received from stock options exercised during 2006 was $975.7 million and the actual tax benefit realized for tax deductions from stock options exercised totaled $111.9 million. The Company uses treasury shares
purchased under the Company&#146;s historical share repurchase program to satisfy share-based exercises. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A summary of the status of the
Company&#146;s stock option grants as of December&nbsp;31, 2006, 2005 and 2004, and changes during the years then ended, is presented in the following table: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>RSUs </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">RSUs
generally vest 100% on the third anniversary of the grant and are payable in either shares of McDonald&#146;s common stock or cash, at the Company&#146;s discretion. Certain executives have been awarded RSUs that are performance-based vesting. The
fair value of each RSU granted is equal to the market price of the Company&#146;s stock at date of grant less the present value of expected dividends over the vesting period. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A summary of the Company&#146;s RSU activity during the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2006 and 2005 is presented in the following table: </FONT></P> <P

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>
<A NAME="tx88993_28"></A>MANAGEMENT&#146;S REPORT </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Management is responsible for the preparation, integrity and fair presentation of the consolidated
financial statements and Notes to the consolidated financial statements. The financial statements were prepared in accordance with the accounting principles generally accepted in the U.S. and include certain amounts based on management&#146;s
judgment and best estimates. Other financial information presented is consistent with the financial statements. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Management is also responsible for
establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over financial reporting as defined in Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f) under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934. The Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting is designed under the
supervision of the Company&#146;s principal executive and financial officers in order to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance
with generally accepted accounting principles. The Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(i)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of assets of the Company; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(ii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles,
and that receipts and expenditures of the Company are being made only in accordance with authorizations of management and directors of the Company; and </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(iii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use or disposition of the Company&#146;s assets that could have a material effect
on the financial statements. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over financial reporting may not prevent or detect
misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may
deteriorate. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Management assessed the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting as of December&nbsp;31, 2006. In making
this assessment, management used the criteria established in Internal Control&#150;Integrated Framework issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission (COSO). </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Based on our assessment and those criteria, management believes that the Company maintained effective internal control over financial reporting as of December&nbsp;31,
2006. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Company&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm, Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP, has issued an attestation report on management&#146;s
assessment of the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. That report appears on a subsequent page of this Report and expresses unqualified opinions on management&#146;s assessment and on the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s
internal control over financial reporting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">McDONALD&#146;S CORPORATION </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">February&nbsp;19, 2007 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

audit also includes assessing the accounting principles used and significant estimates made by management, as well as evaluating the overall financial statement presentation. We believe that our audits provide a reasonable basis for our opinion.

McDonald&#146;s Corporation at December&nbsp;31, 2006 and 2005, and the consolidated results of its operations and its cash flows for each of the three years in the period ended December&nbsp;31, 2006, in conformity with U.S. generally accepted
accounting principles. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As discussed in the Notes to the consolidated financial statements, on December&nbsp;31, 2006, the Company adopted the provisions

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>
<A NAME="tx88993_30"></A>REPORT OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM ON INTERNAL CONTROL OVER FINANCIAL REPORTING </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We have audited
management&#146;s assessment, included in the accompanying Management&#146;s Report, that McDonald&#146;s Corporation maintained effective internal control over financial reporting as of December&nbsp;31, 2006, based on criteria established in
Internal Control-Integrated Framework issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission (the COSO criteria). The Company&#146;s management is responsible for maintaining effective internal control over financial
reporting and for its assessment of the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting. Our responsibility is to express an opinion on management&#146;s assessment and an opinion on the effectiveness of the Company&#146;s internal
control over financial reporting based on our audit. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We conducted our audit in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight
Board (United States). Those standards require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about whether effective internal control over financial reporting was maintained in all material respects. Our audit included obtaining
an understanding of internal control over financial reporting, evaluating management&#146;s assessment, testing and evaluating the design and operating effectiveness of internal control, and performing such other procedures as we considered
necessary in the circumstances. We believe that our audit provides a reasonable basis for our opinion. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A company&#146;s internal control over financial
reporting is a process designed to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. A
company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that (1)&nbsp;pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the
assets of the company; (2)&nbsp;provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, and that receipts and expenditures of
the company are being made only in accordance with authorizations of management and directors of the company; and (3)&nbsp;provide reasonable assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition of the
company&#146;s assets that could have a material effect on the financial statements. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Because of its inherent limitations, internal control over financial
reporting may not prevent or detect misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of effectiveness to future periods are subject to the risk that controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree of compliance
with the policies or procedures may deteriorate. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In our opinion, management&#146;s assessment that the Company maintained effective internal control over
financial reporting as of December&nbsp;31, 2006, is fairly stated, in all material respects, based on the COSO criteria. Also in our opinion, the Company maintained, in all material respects, effective internal control over financial reporting as
of December&nbsp;31, 2006, based on the COSO criteria. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We have also audited, in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Standards
Board (United States), the Consolidated balance sheets of McDonald&#146;s Corporation as of December&nbsp;31, 2006 and 2005, and the related Consolidated statements of income, shareholders&#146; equity and cash flows for each of the three years in
the period ended December&nbsp;31, 2006 and our report dated February&nbsp;19, 2007 expressed an unqualified opinion thereon. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">ERNST&nbsp;&amp; YOUNG LLP
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Chicago, Illinois </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">February 19, 2007 </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">48 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>
<A NAME="tx88993_12"></A>ITEM&nbsp;9. CHANGES IN AND DISAGREEMENTS WITH ACCOUNTANTS ON ACCOUNTING AND FINANCIAL DISCLOSURE </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">None. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>
<A NAME="tx88993_13"></A>ITEM&nbsp;9A. CONTROLS AND PROCEDURES </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Disclosure controls </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">An evaluation was conducted under the supervision and with the participation of the Company&#146;s management, including the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) and Chief Financial Officer (CFO), of the effectiveness of the
design and operation of the Company&#146;s disclosure controls and procedures as of December&nbsp;31, 2006. Based on that evaluation, the CEO and CFO concluded that the Company&#146;s disclosure controls and procedures were effective as of such date
to ensure that information required to be disclosed in the reports that it files or submits under the Exchange Act is recorded, processed, summarized and reported within the time periods specified in Securities and Exchange Commission rules and
forms. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Internal control over financial reporting </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The
Company&#146;s management, including the CEO and CFO, confirm that there was no change in the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting during the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2006 that has materially affected, or is reasonably
likely to materially affect, the Company&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Management&#146;s report </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Management&#146;s report and the Report of independent registered public accounting firm on internal control over financial reporting are set forth in Part II,
Item&nbsp;8 of this Form 10-K. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>
<A NAME="tx88993_14"></A>ITEM&nbsp;9B. OTHER INFORMATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">None. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>PART III </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>
<A NAME="tx88993_15"></A>ITEM&nbsp;10. DIRECTORS, EXECUTIVE OFFICERS AND CORPORATE GOVERNANCE </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Information regarding directors and the Company&#146;s
Code of Conduct for the Board of Directors, its Code of Ethics for Chief Executive Officer and Senior Financial Officers and its Standards of Business Conduct are incorporated herein by reference from the Company&#146;s definitive proxy statement,
which will be filed no later than 120 days after December&nbsp;31, 2006. We will post any amendments to or any waivers for directors and executive officers from provisions of the Codes on our website at www.governance.mcdonalds.com. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Information regarding all of the Company&#146;s executive officers is included in Part I, page 7 of this Form 10-K. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>

which will be filed no later than 120 days after December&nbsp;31, 2006. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>

herein by reference from the Company&#146;s definitive proxy statement, which will be filed no later than 120 days after December&nbsp;31, 2006. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>

<DESCRIPTION>EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT BETWEEN DENIS HENNEQUIN AND THE COMPANY

<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Employment Contract between Denis Hennequin and the Company</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

<DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-right:1%; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B>
<A NAME="tx_p88993_22"></A>EXHIBIT 10(p). </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>CONTRAT DE TRAVAIL </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ENTRE LES SOUSSIGNES </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">La Societ&eacute; <B>McDONALD&#146; S SYSTEM OF FRANCE, INC,</B> soci&eacute;t&eacute; de droit
am&eacute;ricain dont le si&egrave;ge social est sis Prentice Hall Corporation System Inc., 2711 Centerville Road, Suite 400, Wilmington, Delaware, 19808, repr&eacute;sent&eacute;e en France par sa succursale de droit am&eacute;ricain sise 1, rue
Gustave Eiffel - 78045 Guyancourt cedex, repr&eacute;sent&eacute;e aux pr&eacute;sentes par Monsieur Matthew H. Paull agissant en qualit&eacute; de Vice Pr&eacute;sident et de Contr&ocirc;leur de la Soci&eacute;t&eacute;, (Ci-apr&egrave;s: la
soci&eacute;t&eacute;) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>D&#146;UNE PART, </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ET
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Monsieur Denis HENNEQUIN,</B> de nationalit&eacute; fran&ccedil;aise, immatricul&eacute; &agrave; la s&eacute;curit&eacute; sociale sous le
num&eacute;ro XXXXXXXXXX, domicili&eacute; XXXXXXXXXXXXXX. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>D&#146;AUTRE PART, </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Il a &eacute;t&eacute; convenu et arr&ecirc;t&eacute; ce qui suit: </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Le pr&eacute;sent contrat actualise le
contrat de travail de Monsieur HENNEQUIN afin de rappeler et d&#146;ent&eacute;riner les conditions actuelles de son emploi. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Depuis le 3 d&eacute;cembre
1984, les fonctions de Monsieur HENNEQUIN ont r&eacute;guli&egrave;rement &eacute;volu&eacute;es, sans interruption, jusqu&#146;&agrave; sa position actuelle de Pr&eacute;sident Europe. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 1 : Engagement </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN exerce les fonctions de Pr&eacute;sident Europe, position Cadre.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Il est express&eacute;ment convenu que l&#146;anciennet&eacute; de Monsieur HENNEQUIN est prise en compte depuis le 3 d&eacute;cembre 1984, date &agrave;
laquelle il a commenc&eacute; &agrave; travailler avec le Groupe McDonald&#146;s (d&eacute;fini comme comprenant la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; McDonald&#146;s Corporation ainsi que toutes les filiales qu&#146;elle d&eacute;tient &agrave; cent pour cent).
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Il est tenu compte de cette date pour la d&eacute;termination de l&#146;ensemble des droits de Monsieur HENNEQUIN li&eacute;s &agrave;
l&#146;anciennet&eacute;. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-bottom:3px;line-height:95%; vertical-align:top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A seul titre informatif, il est sp&eacute;cifi&eacute; que la
Soci&eacute;t&eacute; applique &agrave; titre volontaire la convention collective des bureaux d&#146;Etudes Techniques, Cabinets d&#146;Ing&eacute;nieurs-Conseils, Soci&eacute;t&eacute;s de Conseils Nationale dans ses dispositions &eacute;tendues
(SYNTEC<B><I><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000"><SUP>(1)</SUP></FONT><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000"></FONT></I></B><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000">). </FONT></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 2 : Attributions </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Le descriptif du poste de
Pr&eacute;sident Europe se trouve en annexe et est consid&eacute;r&eacute;e comme faisant partie int&eacute;grante du pr&eacute;sent contrat. Elle est sign&eacute;e par Monsieur HENNEQUIN. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN doit rendre compte de sa mission aussi souvent que n&eacute;cessaire &agrave; la Direction de la soci&eacute;t&eacute; ou &agrave; toute autre
personne, physique ou morale, d&eacute;sign&eacute;e par cette derni&egrave;re. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Les attributions de Monsieur HENNEQUIN sont amen&eacute;es &agrave;
&eacute;voluer, et lesdites attributions, ainsi que le nom et/ou la qualit&eacute; de la personne &agrave; laquelle Monsieur HENNEQUIN rendra directement compte de son activit&eacute;, pourront &ecirc;tre modifi&eacute;s, autant que
n&eacute;cessaire, compte tenu de l&#146;&eacute;volution de </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></DIV><DIV
STYLE="position:relative;float:right; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B>EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>BETWEEN THE UNDERSIGNED </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B>McDONALD&#146;S SYSTEM OF FRANCE, INC.</B>, a company governed by American law whose registered office is located at Prentice Hall Corporation System, Inc., 2711 Centerville Road, Suite 400, Wilmington, Delaware 19808, represented in
France by its branch McDonald&#146;s System of France, governed by American law and located at 1, rue Gustave Eiffel - 78045 Guyancourt cedex, represented for the purposes hereof by Matthew H. Paull, acting in his capacity as Vice President and
Controller of the Company, (Hereinafter: the Company) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>ON THE ONE HAND, </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>AND </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Mr.&nbsp;Denis HENNEQUIN</B>, a French national, registered with the French social security system under
number XXXXXXXXXXX, residing at XXXXXXXXXXXXXXX. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>ON THE OTHER HAND, </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>It is hereby agreed as follows: </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The present contract is to update Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN&#146;S employment
contract to acknowledge and memorialize the current conditions of his employment. Since December&nbsp;3rd 1984, Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN&#146;S duties have been regularly developed without any interruption until his current position of President Europe.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 1: Hiring </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN holds the
position of President-Europe, with executive employee status. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">It is expressly agreed that Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN&#146;s seniority shall be taken into account
with effect from 3&nbsp;December 1984, which is the date on which he first joined the McDonald&#146;s Group (defined as inclusive of McDonald&#146;s Corporation and all whollyowned subsidiaries thereof). </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This date shall be used as a reference in order to determine all Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN&#146;s entitlements based on length of service. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-bottom:3px;line-height:95%; vertical-align:top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For information purposes, it is specified that the Company has chosen to apply voluntarily the extended provisions
of the national collective bargaining agreement for the IT, engineering and consulting sector (&#147;SYNTEC<B><I><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000"><SUP>(1)</SUP></FONT><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"
COLOR="#000000"></FONT></I></B><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000">&#148;). </FONT></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 2: Duties </U></B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Job description for President - Europe is attached to this employment contract and is considered as an integral part of said contract. It is signed by
Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN reports on the performance of his duties, as often as necessary, to the Management of the Company McDonald&#146;s
Corporation or to any other natural person or legal entity designated by the latter. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The duties of Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN may evolve over time and said
duties, as well as the person and/or the capacity of the person to whom Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN is required directly to report, are subject to change and may be modified as often as necessary to take into account organizational changes within the Group,
provided that these changes are in keeping with Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN&#146;s status. Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN shall be informed of any such changes </FONT></P></DIV><br clear="All">

<DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-right:1%; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">l&#146;organisation du Groupe, dans le respect des qualifications de Monsieur HENNEQUIN. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Tout changement de cette nature sera notifi&eacute; par
Monsieur HENNEQUIN par note interne et ne pourra pas &ecirc;tre consid&eacute;r&eacute; comme une modification du pr&eacute;sent contrat de travail, ce que Monsieur HENNEQUIN accepte express&eacute;ment. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN s&#146;engage &agrave; remplir ses fonctions au mieux des int&eacute;r&ecirc;ts de la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; et du Groupe et conform&eacute;ment
&agrave; leur politique g&eacute;n&eacute;rale, incluant, en particulier, le Code de Pratiques des Affaires (&laquo; Standards of Business Conduct &raquo;) ainsi qu&#146;aux instructions qui lui seront donn&eacute;es par ses sup&eacute;rieurs
hi&eacute;rarchiques. De fa&ccedil;on g&eacute;n&eacute;rale, Monsieur HENNEQUIN s&#146;engage &agrave; consacrer ses meilleurs soins &agrave; l&#146;exercice de la fonction qui lui est confi&eacute;e et &agrave; respecter, dans le cadre de sa
fonction et de ses attributions, toutes instructions orales ou &eacute;crites, g&eacute;n&eacute;rales ou particuli&egrave;res, de la Direction de la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; et du Groupe. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Dans le cadre de cette mission, il est express&eacute;ment convenu que Monsieur HENNEQUIN accepte tout mandat social pouvant lui &ecirc;tre confi&eacute; au titre de l&#146;une des soci&eacute;t&eacute;s du Groupe.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 3 : Dur&eacute;e </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Le pr&eacute;sent
contrat est conclu pour une dur&eacute;e ind&eacute;termin&eacute;e. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 4 : R&eacute;mun&eacute;ration </U></B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-bottom:3px;line-height:95%; vertical-align:top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A compter du 1</FONT><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="1" COLOR="#000000"><SUP>er</SUP></FONT><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000"> mars 2007, Monsieur HENNEQUIN per&ccedil;oit en r&eacute;mun&eacute;ration de son travail un salaire brut mensuel fixe de 34.615,39 &#128;uros (trente-quatre mille, six cent quinze point trente-neuf
euros). Cette r&eacute;mun&eacute;ration inclut les primes conventionnelles. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN per&ccedil;oit en outre un &#147;treizi&egrave;me
mois&#148; &eacute;gal &agrave; la mensualit&eacute; d&eacute;finie ci-dessus. Cette gratification lui est vers&eacute;e suivant les modalit&eacute;s en vigueur dans l&#146;entreprise. En cas de rupture du pr&eacute;sent contrat, Monsieur HENNEQUIN
percevra ce treizi&egrave;me mois prorata temporis, au cours de l&#146;ann&eacute;e consid&eacute;r&eacute;e. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN per&ccedil;oit en outre,
compte tenu de son statut, une r&eacute;mun&eacute;ration variable dont le montant est fix&eacute; en fonction d&#146;objectifs d&eacute;finis, &agrave; titre informatif, en annexe au pr&eacute;sent contrat. Monsieur HENNEQUIN reconna&icirc;t et
accepte que ces objectifs et crit&egrave;res pourront &ecirc;tre modifi&eacute;s &agrave; tout moment ou annuellement en application de la Politique du Groupe et que ces modifications ne constituent pas une modification de son contrat de travail.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN continuera &eacute;galement &agrave; percevoir une prime d&#146;expatriation lors de ses d&eacute;placements professionnels &agrave;
l&#146;&eacute;tranger. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN b&eacute;n&eacute;ficiera &eacute;galement d&#146;une voiture de fonction selon la politique de McDonald&#146;s
France. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 5 : Dur&eacute;e du travail </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Compte tenu des responsabilit&eacute;s qui sont attribu&eacute;es &agrave; Monsieur HENNEQUIN, dont l&#146;importance implique une large ind&eacute;pendance dans l&#146;organisation de son emploi du temps, de son habilitation &agrave;
prendre des d&eacute;cisions de fa&ccedil;on largement autonome et de la r&eacute;mun&eacute;ration qu&#146;il per&ccedil;oit, qui se trouve dans les niveaux de r&eacute;mun&eacute;ration les plus &eacute;lev&eacute;s de l&#146;entreprise, il est
convenu express&eacute;ment entre les parties que Monsieur HENNEQUIN sera consid&eacute;r&eacute; comme cadre dirigeant au regard des dispositions relatives &agrave; la dur&eacute;e du travail et, &agrave; ce titre, exclu du b&eacute;n&eacute;fice
desdites dispositions. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:right; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">by internal memoranda. Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN expressly acknowledges that said changes shall not be considered as a modification of this employment contract. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN undertakes to perform his duties in the best interests of the Company and the Group and in compliance with the general policies of the latter,
including but not limited to the Standards of Business Conduct, and the instructions given to him by his superiors. Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN undertakes to devote the necessary care and attention to the duties entrusted to him and to follow all the verbal,
written, general or special instructions given to him by the Management of the Company and the Group, provided they are within the scope of the duties and responsibilities entrusted to him. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For the purposes of his duties, it is expressly agreed that Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN shall agree to be appointed as a corporate officer and/or Director of any company of the
Group. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 3: Term </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This contract is
entered into for an unlimited period. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 4: Compensation </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As of 1&nbsp;March 2007, in consideration for the performance of his duties, Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN receives a fixed monthly salary of 34,615.39 &#128;uros gross. This compensation includes the bonuses provided for in the
collective bargaining agreement. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN shall also receive a &#147;thirteenth month&#148; salary payment, equal to one month of salary as
defined above. This amount shall be paid to him in accordance with the terms and conditions in force from time to time in the Company. In the event of termination of this employment contract, the amount of this thirteenth month payment shall be
prorated to the time effectively worked by Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN during the year in question. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN shall also receive a variable compensation
according to his level based on his achievement of the targets as stipulated in, for informational purposes only, an appendix to this contract. Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN acknowledges and agrees that such targets and criteria may be changed from time to
time or year-to-year in conformance with Group policy and that such changes shall not constitute a modification of this employment contract. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN shall also continue to receive allowance expatriation when he shall go abroad for business reasons. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN shall
have benefit of a company car according to the policies of McDonald&#146;s France. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 5: Working time </U></B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Given the importance of the responsibilities entrusted to Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN, which imply that he will have a great deal of freedom to organize his work schedule and take
autonomous decisions, as well as the level of his compensation which is amongst the highest in the Company, it is expressly agreed that Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN is considered as a managing executive and consequently, he is not subject to the provisions on
working time. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 6: Paid vacation </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN&#146;s paid vacation entitlements shall be in accordance with the relevant legal provisions. </FONT></P></DIV><br clear="All"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">54 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-right:1%; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 6 : Cong&eacute;s pay&eacute;s </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN b&eacute;n&eacute;ficie des dispositions l&eacute;gales applicables en
mati&egrave;re de cong&eacute;s pay&eacute;s. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 7 : Lieu de travail </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN est rattach&eacute; administrativement &agrave; la succursale fran&ccedil;aise de la soci&eacute;t&eacute; sise &agrave; Guyancourt o&ugrave; il exerce, &agrave; titre principal, son
activit&eacute;. Toutefois, il est express&eacute;ment convenu que la nature des fonctions de Monsieur HENNEQUIN peut l&#146;amener &agrave; exercer temporairement sa mission en tout autre lieu en France ou &agrave; l&#146;&eacute;tranger.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">En cons&eacute;quence, Monsieur HENNEQUIN s&#146;engage notamment &agrave; effectuer tous d&eacute;placements n&eacute;cessaires &agrave; l&#146;exercice
de ses fonctions, tant en France qu&#146;&agrave; l&#146;&eacute;tranger, et ce quelle que soit leur dur&eacute;e. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 8 : Clause de
mobilit&eacute; </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">La soci&eacute;t&eacute; se r&eacute;serve la possibilit&eacute; de modifier le lieu de travail et de muter Monsieur HENNEQUIN dans
tout autre &eacute;tablissement ou soci&eacute;t&eacute; du Groupe situ&eacute;s dans toutes les zones g&eacute;ographiques en Europe consid&eacute;r&eacute;es comme appartenant, au jour de la signature du pr&eacute;sent contrat, &agrave; &laquo;
McDonald&#146;s Europe &raquo;, sous la seule r&eacute;serve de le pr&eacute;venir au moins six mois &agrave; l&#146;avance. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Les parties au pr&eacute;sent
contrat tiennent &agrave; r&eacute;affirmer l&#146;importance de la mobilit&eacute; dont Monsieur HENNEQUIN doit faire preuve dans l&#146;exercice de ses fonctions compte tenu de la multitude des lieux o&ugrave; s&#146;exerce l&#146;activit&eacute;
du Groupe. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 9 : Remboursement de frais </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Les frais professionnels, notamment de d&eacute;placement, de Monsieur HENNEQUIN, engag&eacute;s &agrave; l&#146;occasion de l&#146;exercice de ses fonctions, dans l&#146;int&eacute;r&ecirc;t de la Soci&eacute;t&eacute;, lui seront
rembours&eacute;s sur pr&eacute;sentation des notes de frais accompagn&eacute;e des justificatifs appropri&eacute;s, conform&eacute;ment aux proc&eacute;dures en vigueur dans la Soci&eacute;t&eacute;, dont il d&eacute;clare avoir pris connaissance.
Le remboursement est effectu&eacute; une fois par mois. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">La Soci&eacute;t&eacute; se r&eacute;serve &agrave; tout moment la possibilit&eacute; de modifier
les modalit&eacute;s de remboursement des frais professionnels, sans que cette modification puisse &ecirc;tre consid&eacute;r&eacute;e comme une modifi cation du contrat par Monsieur HENNEQUIN. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 10 : Exclusivit&eacute; </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN
d&eacute;clare n&#146;exercer aucune autre activit&eacute; professionnelle, autres que celles exerc&eacute;es au titre du pr&eacute;sent contrat, r&eacute;mun&eacute;r&eacute;e ou non, ni d&eacute;tenir aucun mandat social de Directeur dans toute
soci&eacute;t&eacute; du Groupe. L&#146;acceptation par Monsieur HENNEQUIN de toute autre activit&eacute; professionnelle doit faire l&#146;objet d&#146;une autorisation &eacute;crite pr&eacute;alable de la Direction. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 11 : Discr&eacute;tion/ Confidentialit&eacute; </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN reconna&icirc;t que la divulgation d&#146;informations confidentielles ou de secrets commerciaux de la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; et/ ou de toute soci&eacute;t&eacute; du Groupe pourrait nuire aux int&eacute;r&ecirc;ts de ces
derniers. Ceci concerne, notamment : </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(a)&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">toutes les versions de logiciels, de mat&eacute;riel informatique, de progiciels et de documents dont la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; et/ ou toute soci&eacute;t&eacute; du Groupe sont
propri&eacute;taires (y compris les codes sources et les codes objet) ; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:right; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 7: Place of work </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">From an administrative point of view, Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN is attached to the French
branch of the Company in Guyancourt, where he will perform the major part of his duties. However, it is expressly agreed that, due to the nature of these duties, he may be required to work on a temporary basis at any other place in France or abroad.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As a result, Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN undertakes to travel as often and for as long as necessary for professional purposes, both in France and abroad.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 8: Mobility clause </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Company
reserves the right to change the place of work of Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN and to transfer the latter to any other establishment or company of the Group in a country within the geographical area that is as of the date of this contract considered
&#147;McDonald&#146;s Europe&#148;, subject to at least six months&#146; prior notice. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The parties hereto stress the importance of
Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN&#146;s acceptance of these provisions regarding mobility, in view of the number of sites operated by the Group. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 9:
Reimbursement of business expenses </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The business expenses, and in particular the travel expenses incurred by Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN for the purposes of
his duties and in the Company&#146;s interests, shall be reimbursed to him upon the presentation of expense sheets along with supporting documents, in compliance with the Company&#146;s business expenses policy, Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN representing that
he understands and accepts same. Business expenses are reimbursed on a monthly basis. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The Company reserves the right to change the terms and conditions of
its business expenses policy at any time, without said change being considered as a modification of Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN&#146;s employment contract. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 10: Exclusivity </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN represents that he does not and will not perform any other professional activities,
either with or without compensation, other than pursuant to his employment under this contract or as corporate officer or Director of any Group company. Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN shall not agree to undertake any other professional activities without the
prior written consent of the Management. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 11: Secrecy/Confidentiality </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN acknowledges that the disclosure of the Company&#146;s and/or Group&#146;s confidential information or trade secrets could be detrimental to the interests of the Company and/or Group. This
obligation of secrecy/confidentiality shall apply, in particular, to: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

Groupe ainsi que celles de leurs clients, fournisseurs et partenaires. Ceci s&#146;applique tant pendant la dur&eacute;e du pr&eacute;sent contrat qu&#146;apr&egrave;s sa cessation, sur une p&eacute;riode illimit&eacute;e. A cet effet, Monsieur
HENNEQUIN ne peut en aucun cas divulguer &agrave; un quelconque tiers, ni utiliser pour son usage personnel, les informations techniques ou commerciales confidentielles relatives &agrave; la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; et au Groupe. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 12 : Droits de propri&eacute;t&eacute; intellectuelles et/ ou industrielles </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Si dans l&#146;exercice de ses fonctions, qui comportent une mission inventive, Monsieur HENNEQUIN r&eacute;alisait une invention quelconque, brevetable ou non, cr&eacute;ait des dessins ou mod&egrave;les,
m&eacute;thodes, programmes, formules ou proc&eacute;d&eacute;s ayant trait aux activit&eacute;s, &eacute;tudes ou recherches de la soci&eacute;t&eacute; et susceptibles d&#146;&ecirc;tre prot&eacute;g&eacute;s, les droits de propri&eacute;t&eacute;
intellectuelle ou industrielle en r&eacute;sultant appartiendrait de plein droit &agrave; la Soci&eacute;t&eacute;. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN s&#146;engage, en
tout &eacute;tat de cause, &agrave; n&#146;effectuer aucune d&eacute;marche ni proc&eacute;dure visant &agrave; se faire reconna&icirc;tre ou &agrave; se faire r&eacute;server un droit de propri&eacute;t&eacute; intellectuelle quel qu&#146;il soit
(droit d&#146;auteur, copyright, brevet, dessin et mod&egrave;le, marque), ou un quelconque droit d&#146;usage ou d&#146;exploitation, sur les produits ou proc&eacute;d&eacute;s pr&eacute;cit&eacute;s de sa cr&eacute;ation ou de son invention, dans
quelque pays que ce soit, tant en ex&eacute;cution du pr&eacute;sent contrat qu&#146;apr&egrave;s l&#146;ach&egrave;vement de celui-ci. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN
a bien conscience de ce que toute violation de la pr&eacute;sente obligation engagerait n&eacute;cessairement sa responsabilit&eacute; contractuelle. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 13 : Non- sollicitation du personnel </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Aussi bien pendant la dur&eacute;e du pr&eacute;sent contrat qu&#146;apr&egrave;s sa
rupture par l&#146;une ou l&#146;autre des parties et pour quelque motif que ce soit, Monsieur HENNEQUIN s&#146;engage &agrave; ne pas, directement ou indirectement, convaincre ou tenter de convaincre un quelconque employ&eacute; de la
Soci&eacute;t&eacute; ou de toute autre soci&eacute;t&eacute; du groupe qu&#146;elle pourra former ou dont elle pourra faire partie, &agrave; la date de cessation de son contrat, de quitter son emploi ou de travailler pour ou fournir des services
&agrave; une quelconque autre personne physique ou morale, en quelque qualit&eacute; que ce soit. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">56 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
</DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:right; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:8%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">prospective clients, files and data regarding suppliers and corporate strategies; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(d)&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">information provided by the Company&#146;s and/or any Group company&#146;s suppliers, employees, consultants, clients or business partners for review, evaluation or use;
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(e)&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">all other information not generally known to the general public, which if misused or disclosed, could reasonably be expected to adversely affect the Company&#146;s and/or any Group
company&#146;s business. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN keeps the Company&#146;s and any Group company&#146;s trade secrets (and those of any individual
or legal entity contracting with the Company), whether or not prepared or developed by him, in the strictest confidence. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN is bound by a
general duty of discretion and secrecy regarding the Company&#146;s business and that of the Group as well as those of their clients, suppliers and business partners. This obligation shall apply both during the performance of this contract and
following the termination hereof for an unlimited period. Consequently, Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN agrees not to disclose to any third party or use for his own private purposes, any confidential technical or commercial information relating to the Company or
the Group. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 12: Intellectual and/or industrial property rights </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If, during the performance of his duties, Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN makes any invention, whether patentable or not, or creates any design or model, method, program, formula or process relating to the activities, studies or
research of the Company which is capable of being protected, the resulting intellectual or industrial property rights would automatically belong to the Company. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">In any event, Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN agrees not to take any steps or implement any procedures aimed at obtaining title to or the reservation of an intellectual property right of any kind whatsoever (author&#146;s rights, copyright, patent,
design, model, trademark) or any right of use or exploitation over the aforementioned products or processes or over the creation or invention thereof. This undertaking shall apply in all countries, both during the performance of this contract and
following the termination thereof. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN is aware of the fact that he shall be held contractually liability for any violation of this
obligation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 13: Non-solicitation </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">During the performance of this contract or following its termination at the initiative of either party and for any reason whatsoever, Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN undertakes not to, either directly or indirectly, convince or attempt to convince any
person employed by the Company or by any company of the Group it may form or belong to at the time of termination, to leave their employment or to work for or provide services to any other individual or legal entity, in any capacity whatsoever.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 14: Termination </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This employment
contract may be terminated at the initiative of either of the parties subject to a mutual notice period of three months, except that it may be terminated by the Company without notice in the event of serious misconduct (&#147;faute grave&#148;),
gross misconduct (&#147;faute lourde&#148;) or force majeure. </FONT></P></DIV><br clear="All">

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-right:1%; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 14 : Cessation du contrat </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Le pr&eacute;sent contrat de travail pourra &ecirc;tre rompu &agrave; l&#146;initiative de
l&#146;une ou l&#146;autre des parties moyennant le respect d&#146;un pr&eacute;avis r&eacute;ciproque de trois mois, hormis dans les cas o&ugrave; la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; d&eacute;cidera de rompre le contrat de travail pour faute grave, lourde ou
&eacute;v&eacute;nement de force majeure. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">En cas de cessation du pr&eacute;sent contrat de travail, pour un quelconque motif (licenciement,
d&eacute;mission, d&eacute;part en retraite, etc.), Monsieur HENNEQUIN s&#146;engage &agrave; restituer &agrave; la Soci&eacute;t&eacute;, de sa propre initiative, tout le mat&eacute;riel ainsi que tout fichier et autres documents (y compris toutes
photocopies de ceux-ci) qu&#146;il pourra avoir en sa possession ou sous son contr&ocirc;le en rapport avec ses activit&eacute;s professionnelles pour le compte de la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; et/ ou de toute Soci&eacute;t&eacute; du Groupe et/ou avec
les activit&eacute;s professionnelles de ses clients. Cette restitution interviendra au terme du pr&eacute;avis sauf si celui-ci n&#146;est pas ex&eacute;cut&eacute; quelle qu&#146;en soit la raison. Dans cette derni&egrave;re hypoth&egrave;se, la
restitution interviendra dans les 48 heures suivant la notification de la rupture du contrat. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">En cas de suspension du contrat de travail, pour quelque
raison que ce soit et quelle que soit la dur&eacute;e de cette suspension, Monsieur HENNEQUIN devra &eacute;galement restituer, &agrave; la soci&eacute;t&eacute;, &agrave; la premi&egrave;re demande notifi&eacute;e par la soci&eacute;t&eacute; par
tout moyen, tous les &eacute;l&eacute;ments vis&eacute;s ci-dessus. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 15 : accords ant&eacute;rieurs </U></B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Le pr&eacute;sent contrat constitue l&#146;int&eacute;gralit&eacute; des accords entre les parties. Il annule et remplace tout accord ant&eacute;rieur conclu directement
ou indirectement, tant &eacute;crit que verbal, entre la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; et Monsieur HENNEQUIN, et/ou les &eacute;ventuels engagements, directs ou indirects, de l&#146;une des parties &agrave; l&#146;&eacute;gard de l&#146;autre. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Monsieur HENNEQUIN informera sans d&eacute;lai la Soci&eacute;t&eacute; de toute modification des informations qu&#146;il lui aura donn&eacute;es lors de son embauche
(adresse, etc.). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 16 : Loi applicable </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Le pr&eacute;sent contrat de travail sera r&eacute;gi par le droit fran&ccedil;ais, tant pour sa conclusion que pour son ex&eacute;cution et sa cessation. Tout litige y aff&eacute;rent sera soumis &agrave; la comp&eacute;tence exclusive des
tribunaux fran&ccedil;ais. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Les engagements pris de part et d&#146;autre assurent les int&eacute;r&ecirc;ts de chacun, les parties confirmeront leur accord
sans r&eacute;serve sur les termes de la pr&eacute;sente et s&#146;engageront &agrave; respecter loyalement les droits et obligations qui en r&eacute;sultent. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Pour la bonne r&egrave;gle, Monsieur HENNEQUIN retournera l&#146;un des deux exemplaires ci-joints, rev&ecirc;tu de sa signature pr&eacute;c&eacute;d&eacute;e de la mention &laquo; lu et approuv&eacute; &raquo;. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Fait &agrave; <U></U>Paris, France, le February 26, 2007 </FONT></P>

other documents (including photocopies) in his possession or under his control relating to his professional activities for the Company and/or any Group company and/or the professional activities of its clients. This equipment shall be returned at
the end of the notice period, unless the notice period is not worked out for any reason whatsoever, in which case the equipment shall be returned within 48 hours of the date of the written notice of termination. </FONT></P> <P

equipment to the Company by any appropriate means upon the first request of the latter. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 15: Prior agreements </U></B></FONT></P> <P

Company and Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN and/or any commitments made, directly or indirectly, by either party towards the other. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN shall
immediately inform the Company of any change to the information given to the latter at the time he was hired (address, etc.). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Article 16: Governing

relation hereto shall be submitted to the French courts. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The commitments made herein are done so in the mutual interests of the parties, who confirm the
term and conditions of this contract without reservation and undertake to abide by the ensuing rights and obligations. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mr.&nbsp;HENNEQUIN shall return one
of the enclosed copies to us for the Company&#146;s files, bearing his signature preceded by the words &#147;read and approved&#148;. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Executed in
