<DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-right:1%; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Annexe 1 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center">

<IMG SRC="g88993001.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>McDONALD&#146;S CORPORATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>DEFINITION DE POSTE </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Date : <U>janvier 2007</U> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Lieu :<U> Europe</U> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Fonction : <U>Pr&eacute;sident - McDonald&#146;s Europe</U> </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Sous la supervision du : <U>Pr&eacute;sident directeur g&eacute;n&eacute;ral</U> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U><I>(President and COO)</I></U> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U><B>ETENDUE</B></U> : (fonctions et nombre de subordonn&eacute;s) </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A la responsabilit&eacute; globale de la croissance et du d&eacute;veloppe-ment durables &agrave; long terme de McDonald&#146;s en Europe, y compris la supervision
directe et la responsabilit&eacute; des Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions europ&eacute;ennes de Mc Donald&#146;s et indirectement des Directeurs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux. Aligne l&#146;organisation de McDonald&#146;s en Europe avec le programme de
r&eacute;ussite &laquo; Plan to Win &raquo;, en privil&eacute;giant l&#146;image d&#146;une implantation locale des restaurants au sein du r&eacute;seau mondial de McDonald&#146;s, en am&eacute;liorant notablement l&#146;image du groupe en tant
qu&#146;employeur, les pratiques en mati&egrave;re d&#146;exploitation, de finances, de formation et de ressources humaines. Est responsable de la gestion des talents et du d&eacute;veloppement du leadership des Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions
europ&eacute;ennes et, indirectement des Directeurs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux. Doit s&#146;assurer du renforcement de la confiance des salari&eacute;s, des clients et des parties prenantes dans chaque pays. Prend les d&eacute;cisions difficiles en
s&#146;engageant personnellement et en assumant leur issue. G&egrave;re avec rigueur les rapports professionnels cl&eacute;s en se concentrant sur le climat social. Communique une vision f&eacute;d&eacute;ratrice de l&#146;avenir de McDonald&#146;s
en Europe gr&acirc;ce &agrave; son leadership, en amenant les autres &agrave; suivre la voie du changement. Exige des Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions et des Directeurs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux qu&#146;ils alignent leur organisation sur le &laquo; Plan
to Win &raquo; et qu&#146;ils appliquent ce programme dans tous ses aspects sur leurs march&eacute;s. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U><B>OBJET</B></U> <B>:</B> (grandes lignes et
raisons du poste) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Offre un leadership et des orientations aux Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions europ&eacute;ennes et aux Directeurs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux
afin d&#146;optimiser les r&eacute;sultats de McDonald&#146;s dans leur pays respectif. Evalue les plans strat&eacute;giques afin de s&#146;assurer que l&#146;accent sera mis sur la croissance durable &agrave; long terme, la gestion des talents et
l&#146;&eacute;volution du personnel, la conformit&eacute; au &laquo; Plan to Win &raquo;, l&#146;innovation dans l&#146;exploitation des restaurants gr&acirc;ce &agrave; l&#146;am&eacute;lioration perp&eacute;tuelle des normes de QSP
(qualit&eacute;, service et propret&eacute;), en atteignant les objectifs en termes de r&eacute;sultat d&#146;exploitation, de ventes et de b&eacute;n&eacute;fices. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U><B>PRINCIPALES ATTRIBUTIONS</B></U> <B>:</B> (liste des principaux objectifs fi naux du poste) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Planification
strat&eacute;gique - Evalue les plans strat&eacute;giques pour McDonald&#146;s en Europe pour les rendre conformes au &laquo; Plan to Win &raquo;. Offre un leadership et une assistance aux Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions europ&eacute;ennes et aux
Directeurs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux dans la mise en &#156;uvre de ces plans. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></DIV><DIV
STYLE="position:relative;float:right; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Appendix 1 </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center">

<IMG SRC="g88993001.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>McDONALD&#146;S CORPORATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>POSITION/PERFORMANCE DESCRIPTION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Date: <U>January 2007</U> </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Location: <U>Europe</U> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Title: <U>President - McDonald&#146;s Europe</U>
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Reports to: <U>President and Chief Operating Officer</U> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><U><B>DIMENSIONS</B></U><B>:</B> (Job titles and numbers of people supervised) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Overall responsibility and accountability for driving
McDonald&#146;s sustainable, long-term growth and development in Europe, including direct supervision of and accountability for McDonald&#146;s European Division Presidents and indirectly for Managing Directors. Aligns McDonald&#146;s in Europe
around the Plan to Win, focusing on promoting McDonald&#146;s as local businesses that are part of a global network, driven to dramatically improve employment image, operations, finances, training and people practices. Responsible for talent
management and leadership development of European Division Presidents and, indirectly, Managing Directors. Responsible for ensuring countries enhance trust with employees, customers and stakeholders. Makes the tough calls with personal
responsibility and ownership of outcomes. Decisively manages key interrelationships with focus on organizational climate. Communicates compelling vision of McDonald&#146;s European future through leadership, drawing others into change process.
Demands of Division Presidents and Managing Directors that they make their organizations align with the Plan to Win and implement each aspect within their markets. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><U><B>POSITION PURPOSE</B></U><B>:</B> (Broad functions - Why does job exist?) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To provide leadership and direction to European Division
Presidents and Managing Directors to maximize the business results of McDonald&#146;s in their countries. Assesses their strategic plans to ensure emphases will be on long-term sustainable growth, talent management and employee development,
alignment around the Plan to Win, innovation in restaurant execution through continuously improving QSC, achieving operating income, sales building and profit goals. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U><B>PRINCIPLE ACCOUNTABILITIES</B></U><B>:</B> (A list of major end results the position is designed to accomplish.) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Strategic Planning - Assesses strategic plans for McDonald&#146;s in Europe for alignment with Plan to Win. Provides leadership and support to European Division Presidents and Managing Directors in their implementation of these plans.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Sustainable Growth - Establishes direction and oversees AOW plans and their implementation to ensure long-term sustainable growth aligned with Plan to
Win. Assesses whether country has the staff and resources needed to ensure that sustainable growth is achieved. </FONT></P></DIV><br clear="All"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">58 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

<DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-right:1%; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Croissance durable - Etablit les orientations et surveille les plans &laquo; AOW &raquo; et leur mise en &#156;uvre afin de s&#146;assurer que la croissance durable &agrave; long terme est en ligne avec le &laquo; Plan to Win &raquo;.
Evalue si le pays concern&eacute; dispose du personnel et des ressources n&eacute;cessaires pour s&#146;assurer que la croissance durable peut &ecirc;tre atteinte. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Gestion des talents et d&eacute;veloppement du leadership &#150; Est responsable des &eacute;valuations de performance des Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions et doit s&#146;assurer que les Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions en font de m&ecirc;me
pour les Directeurs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux. Assure un coaching &agrave; long terme afin de d&eacute;velopper les comp&eacute;tences en mati&egrave;re de leadership des Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions et des Directeurs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux. Elabore
les plans de succession pour les subordonn&eacute;s cl&eacute;s et doit s&#146;assurer que les subordonn&eacute;s &eacute;tablissent des plans de succession pour leurs propres subalternes. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">R&eacute;sultat d&#146;exploitation, ventes et b&eacute;n&eacute;fices - A la responsabilit&eacute; globale de la supervision des initiatives strat&eacute;giques visant
&agrave; atteindre les objectifs mensuels et annuels en termes de r&eacute;sultat d&#146;exploitation, de ventes et de b&eacute;n&eacute;fices. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Conduite
professionnelle - Offre un leadership et une assistance aux Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions et aux Directeurs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux dans le cadre du renforcement de la confiance des salari&eacute;s, des clients et des parties prenantes. Doit
s&#146;assurer que les Pr&eacute;sidents des Divisions et les Directeurs g&eacute;n&eacute;raux exercent leur activit&eacute; conform&eacute;ment au Code de Pratiques des Affaires (&laquo; Standards of Business Conduct &raquo;). Donne des
orientations et des directives afin de s&#146;assurer que tous les pays disposent de plans visant &agrave; am&eacute;liorer de mani&egrave;re coh&eacute;rente l&#146;image du groupe en tant qu&#146;employeur. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>PROFIL</U> : </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exp&eacute;rience et comp&eacute;tences :
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Doit se pr&eacute;valoir d&#146;une exp&eacute;rience r&eacute;ussie en tant que Pr&eacute;sident d&#146;une Division, Directeur g&eacute;n&eacute;ral
ou &agrave; tout autre poste &eacute;quivalent, et doit avoir fait ses preuves en tant que leader ayant permis une croissance durable, une gestion des talents, un d&eacute;veloppement du leadership, une croissance du r&eacute;sultat
d&#146;exploitation et une confiance accrue dans la marque McDonald&#146;s. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Communication : </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Fait preuve de solides qualit&eacute;s de communication, tant &agrave; l&#146;&eacute;crit qu&#146;&agrave; l&#146;oral. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Formation : </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Est de pr&eacute;f&eacute;rence titulaire d&#146;un
dipl&ocirc;me d&#146;une &eacute;cole sup&eacute;rieure de commerce ou d&#146;un dipl&ocirc;me &eacute;quivalent ou poss&egrave;de une exp&eacute;rience &agrave; un poste &eacute;quivalent. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Qualit&eacute;s souhait&eacute;es : </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Fait preuve des plus hautes
comp&eacute;tences en mati&egrave;re de leadership (individuelles et strat&eacute;giques), de prise de d&eacute;cision, de vision, de discernement, d&#146;organisation et de planification, d&#146;adaptation, et de la capacit&eacute; &agrave;
communiquer efficacement avec tous les niveaux de l&#146;organisation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P></DIV><DIV
STYLE="position:relative;float:right; width:48%;padding-right:9px;padding-bottom:4px;overflow:hidden"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Talent Management and Leadership Development - Responsible for
performance evaluations of Division Presidents and that Division Presidents perform same on Managing Directors. Does long-term coaching to develop leadership competencies in Division Presidents and Managing Directors. Develops succession plans for
key subordinates and responsible for ensuring that subordinates develop succession plans for their reports. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Operating Income, Sales and Profits - Overall
responsibility for overseeing strategic initiatives designed to achieve monthly and annual operating income, sales and profit goals. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Business Conduct
&#150; Provides leadership and support to Division Presidents and Managing Directors in enhancing trust with employees, customers and stakeholders. Responsible for ensuring that Division Presidents and Managing Directors conduct business in
conformance with Standards of Business Conduct. Provides direction and guidance to ensure all countries have plans to consistently improve employment image. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B><U>POSITION SPECIFICATIONS: </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Experience and Knowledge: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Should be a successful Division President, Managing Director or equivalent with a proven track record of demonstrated leadership to achieve sustainable growth, talent management, leadership development, operating
income growth and increased trust in Brand McDonald&#146;s. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Communications: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Strong, clear written and verbal communications skills are required. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Education: </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Prefer a college degree in business or related studies, or equivalent work experience. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Desired traits: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Highest Levels of Competency in Leadership (individual and strategic), Decision Making, vision,
sound business judgment, organizing and planning, adaptability, and ability to communicate effectively with all levels in the organization. </FONT></P></DIV><br clear="All"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">59 </FONT></P>

<TYPE>EX-10.(Q)

<FILENAME>dex10q.htm
<DESCRIPTION>ASSIGNMENT AGREEMENT BETWEEN TIMOTHY FENTON AND THE COMPANY
<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Assignment Agreement between Timothy Fenton and the Company</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>EXHIBIT 10(q). </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px">

<IMG SRC="g88993002.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">January 2006 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Tim Fenton
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Dear Tim, </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This letter is to review your salary and
benefits package for your assignment in Hong Kong. The term of the assignment is expected to be approximately three to five years. In Hong Kong, your position will continue to be President APMEA, effective March&nbsp;1, 2006. Your band will continue
to be the Executive Management Band for compensation and benefit purposes. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This letter confirms our mutual understanding of the terms and conditions that
apply to your employment with McDonald&#146;s while on assignment. Such employment is subject, of course, to medical clearances, foreign government entry documents, work/residency permits and/or visas, and your acceptance of the terms and conditions
outlined in this letter. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your compensation and benefits package is designed to provide you with a level of compensation and benefits that is approximately
comparable to your home country of the United States (U.S.). We have taken into consideration the additional costs that you may reasonably anticipate as a result of living in Hong Kong. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The terms and conditions outlined in this letter will be in effect only for the period of this assignment. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Total
Overseas Compensation </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For purposes of this assignment, the U.S. shall be designated as your point of origin or your home country. Hong Kong shall
be designated as your assignment location. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">McDonald&#146;s uses a balance sheet approach to help ensure that your standard of living in Hong Kong will be
reasonably comparable to that which you had in the U.S. A copy of your compensation balance sheet is attached to this letter. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Base Salary
</U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your current annual base salary is $400,000 effective January&nbsp;4, 2005. You will remain on the U.S. payroll and you will continue to follow the
U.S. compensation and benefits programs. You will receive an annual performance and base salary review on March&nbsp;1, 2006 based on your home country guidelines. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><U>Bonus </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You will continue to be eligible to be considered for a bonus under the Corporate Officer target incentive program according to your
level. The performance factor of the bonus computation will continue to be based on a combination of McDonald&#146;s APMEA and Corporate performance. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><U>Long Term Incentives </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You will continue to be eligible for long term incentives based on McDonald&#146;s U.S. guidelines. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Cash Performance Unit Plan </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You will maintain your eligibility in the
Cash Performance Unit Plan based on the plan guidelines. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Cost of Living Allowance </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A cost of living allowance (COLA) is a differential paid to equalize for the difference between the cost of goods and services in the U.S. versus the cost goods and services in Hong Kong. The COLA is determined by an
outside consulting firm and is adjusted as warranted due to changes in prices, fluctuations in exchange rates, base salary and family size. While your COLA will be paid at the same time as your payroll, it can fluctuate from time to time based on
these adjustments. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Housing Allowance </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A budget for
your housing in Hong Kong will be determined. Housing includes rent and utilities excluding telephone, cable television and internet, which are your responsibility. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Housing Contribution </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A housing contribution is an estimated amount that a person with your base salary and family
size would spend on housing (includes assumed utility cost) in the U.S. The amount is determined by an outside consultant at the start of the assignment and is based on base salary and family size. The housing contribution amount is fixed for the
duration of the assignment and does not change unless there is a change in family status. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">60 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your housing contribution has been set at an annual amount of $26,019 for the term of the assignment. This is a reduced
portion of the full housing contribution amount of $48,272. This amount will be deducted from your payroll. Any housing you decide to maintain in the U.S. during your assignment will be your responsibility. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Family Assistance Allowance </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A family assistance allowance is paid to
compensate for additional family costs that arise when relocating outside of your home country. You will receive an annual family assistance allowance for your spouse in the amount of US $5,000 per year and US $1,000 for each additional dependent.
Your family assistance payment will be paid to you through your U.S. payroll on an ongoing basis. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Tax Equalization </U></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You will be tax equalized to ensure that you pay approximately the same amount of taxes that you would have paid in the U.S. McDonald&#146;s will pay your actual U.S. and
Hong Kong tax obligations either directly or by reimbursing you. You will be responsible for paying a &#147;hypothetical&#148; U.S federal and state tax to McDonald&#146;s. Deductions from your paycheck for this &#147;hypothetical&#148; tax should
reflect approximately what you would have paid in tax had you remained working in the U.S. This &#147;hypothetical&#148; tax withholding is only an estimate; your actual tax liabilities may be more or less. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">An accounting firm selected by McDonald&#146;s Corporation will be retained to assist in the preparation of your U.S. and Hong Kong income tax returns. The accounting
firm will calculate a final tax equalization settlement after your tax returns have been completed. At this time, your final tax liability will be determined. Your total hypothetical tax withholding will be compared to this final tax liability as
calculated by the accounting firm to determine whether tax has been overwithheld, in which case McDonald&#146;s will refund the excess withholding to you within 30 days, or whether not enough tax was withheld, in which case you must pay the
additional tax liability to McDonald&#146;s within 30 days. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Relocation Assistance </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You will be eligible to receive the global relocation program for long-term assignments. Please contact Tracy Toth (XXX-XXX-XXXX) in Relocation Services, Oak Brook. She will provide you with relocation assistance
throughout your relocation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Medical Insurance </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">McDonald&#146;s will provide you with medical coverage approximately equivalent to that you had in U.S. You will be removed from the McDonald&#146;s medical plan during the course of your international assignment and will be placed on the
CIGNA International medical program. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The selection of insurance provider and determination of equivalence will be solely within McDonald&#146;s
discretion. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Cultural Training </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You and your family are
eligible for cross-cultural training. Please contact Gaby Gutierrez (XXX-XXX-XXXX) to arrange for cultural training before your move to Hong Kong. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><U>Holidays and Vacation </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You will follow the public holiday schedule in effect in Hong Kong. You will continue the same eligibility for
vacation as under McDonald&#146;s U.S. policy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Automobile </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">McDonald&#146;s China Development Company will provide you with a company car according to its policies. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Home Leave </U></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You and your eligible family members are eligible for home leave. The number of home leave trips for you and your eligible family members is agreed to between you and
Mike Roberts, COO of McDonald&#146;s. McDonald&#146;s will reimburse round-trip coach airfare or lowest available fare (business class airfare for flights over 6 hours in length) from Hong Kong to South Carolina. While you are encouraged to return
home on your leave, you may choose another destination. McDonald&#146;s will reimburse up to the limit of the equivalent airfare of Hong Kong to South Carolina. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><U>Sabbatical Entitlement </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your eligibility for sabbatical will be determined under McDonald&#146;s U.S. policy. If you intend to take your
sabbatical during your assignment, you must give at least 6 months notice and obtain approval prior to taking the sabbatical. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Human Resource Policies
</U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">McDonald&#146;s Corporation&#146;s benefits and compensation guidelines and global assignee policies (including vacation, home leave, and tax
equalization) will apply to you and your family. Such guidelines and policies may be changed from time to time by McDonald&#146;s at its sole discretion. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">61 </FONT></P>

<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Data Protection </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Personal information relating to you and your family in connection with your employment and your overseas assignment will need to be processed and such information may need to be sent between Hong Kong and the U.S. and to other
McDonald&#146;s entities located elsewhere. By signing below, you agree on behalf of yourself and your family members to all such transmittal and processing of this information </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Governing Law </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This assignment letter is governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of
Illinois and the United States, without reference to principles of conflicts of laws. In the event of any dispute arising with respect to this assignment letter, which cannot amicably be resolved, the courts of the United States of America shall
have sole and exclusive jurisdiction over any and all such claims. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Termination while Overseas </U></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your assignment to Hong Kong may be voluntarily ended by you, or involuntarily by McDonald&#146;s Corporation or McDonald&#146;s China Development Company at will, with
or without notice or reason. If your assignment ends for whatever reason and you continue to be an employee of McDonald&#146;s Corporation or a McDonald&#146;s subsidiary or joint venture, McDonald&#146;s will reimburse you for return airfare
(coach/economy class) for you and your eligible dependents and will provide for shipment of your household goods within prescribed limits to your point of origin or, if appropriate, to the place of your next assignment, whether in or outside the
United States. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If you voluntarily terminate your employment with McDonald&#146;s Corporation while on assignment, and do not immediately become an
employee of a McDonald&#146;s subsidiary or joint venture, you are solely responsible for your own relocation and repatriation. If your employment with McDonald&#146;s Corporation is involuntarily terminated while you are on assignment,
McDonald&#146;s will reimburse you for return airfare (coach/economy class) for you and your eligible dependents and will provide for shipment of your household goods within prescribed limits to your point of origin within the U.S. This
reimbursement and shipment is contingent on your moving back to the U.S. within 60 days of termination. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">You understand that this letter is not to be
construed as an employment contract or guarantee of employment for any period of time. Your employment at McDonald&#146;s shall continue to be &#147;at will.&#148; This means that you are free to terminate your employment at any time, for any
reason, and McDonald&#146;s Corporation retains the same right. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>Summary </U></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We wish you success in your global assignment. If you have any questions, please contact Gaby Gutierrez (xxx-xxx-xxxx) or me. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

any money or benefits due to me from McDonald&#146;s to the full extent permitted by law and agree to promptly repay any balance which may remain. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">4.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">I agree to pay any attorney&#146;s fees and costs incurred by McDonald&#146;s in seeking reimbursement, as well as interest on any outstanding balance which I am obligated to repay.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If a homeowner, I hereby state that I and my spouse, if applicable, hold sole title to the property in which I currently reside and it is not subject to any dispute, argument, or
encumbrance including but not limited to, divorce, joint ownership, probate, rental agreement, etc., or any other condition that will affect my ability to convey clear title when it is sold. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">6.</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">If I have been furnished a Company car, I understand the following: </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">a)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For relocations into Home Office or a Division office from a regional office, the personal use charge will generally be higher. In addition, positions at a director level or above
require a one-time, permanent salary reduction to buy into the program. Positions below the director level have the choice of a one-time car loss allowance or a three-year phase out of the company car program. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">For relocations out of Home Office or a Division office to a regional office, the personal use charge will generally be lower. Any permanent salary reduction to buy into the program
will not be refunded. The relocation of a company provided vehicle is contingent provided you will drive a minimum of 18,000 business miles in your new location. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<DESCRIPTION>SECTION 302 CERTIFICATION OF THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER
<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Section 302 Certification of the Chief Executive Officer</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>EXHIBIT 31.1. RULE 13A-14(A) CERTIFICATION OF CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">I, James A. Skinner, Vice Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of McDonald&#146;s Corporation, certify that: </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(1)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">I have reviewed this annual report on Form 10-K of McDonald&#146;s Corporation; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(2)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the
circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(3)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Based on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial condition, results of
operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and for, the periods presented in this report; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(4)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The registrant&#146;s other certifying officer(s) and I are responsible for establishing and maintaining disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Exchange Act Rules
13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e)) and internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f)) for the registrant and have: </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(a)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information
relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(b)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Designed such internal control over financial reporting, or caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our supervision, to provide reasonable
assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
